title: Paul Gonsalves - 1999 - Tell It The Way It Is
description:
Filing a fellwow request, got it somewhere on the net, thanks goes to the original ripper. No artwork.

Gonsalves made his name at the 1956 Newport Jazz Festival with an arresting, 27-chorus solo in the middle of Duke Ellington's performance of "Diminuendo and Crescendo in Blue"

Tell It the Way It Is! was recorded in 1963 by Paul Gonsalves and other two former Duke Ellington band members , Johnny Hodges and Ray Nance, which teamed up with Swedish trumpeter Rolf Ericson and pianist Walter Bishop Jr. on two sessions to create Tell It the Way It Is!.

Performers:
Paul Gonsalves - Tenor Saxophone
Johnny Hodges - Alto Saxophone
Ray Nance - Trumpet / Violin
Rolf Ericson - Trumpet
Walter Bishop Jr - Piano
Ernie Shepard - Bass / vocals
Osie Johnson - drums

Enjoy!
